<subSubSection id="A83E1DFA966534D748DE52BC8DBB86E0" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="26812F3CF7E26C14A26878D6358835F3" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B8863D66678D3A536CCBF5FE94C976EC" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">
An additional, relatively large 
<taxonomicName id="24B5B9DFA1C5F7B3FB9CEE3C62D8800B" class="Actinopterygii" family="Myctophidae" genus="Myctophum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Myctophum" order="Myctophiformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EC468FCA21A1BEA06A09459932834DF2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Myctophum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species of about 3.5 mm in length is observed in the Ichishi Group and will be described separately by one of us (YT). It is characterized by a regularly rounded outline and a relatively long rostrum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
